-- Spanish Unions March in Madrid Against Government Spending Cuts
-- B y   E m m a   R o s s - T h o m a s   a n d   E s t e b a n   D u a r t e
-- 2012-04-29T12:28:56Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-29/spanish-unions-march-in-madrid-against-government-spending-cuts.html
Spain ’s two largest unions led
marches in cities across the country to protest Prime Minister
Mariano Rajoy’s spending cuts, including the reduction of health
care subsidies.  Thousands of people marched to El Sol square in downtown
Madrid, gathering under umbrellas to shelter from the rain.  Comisiones Obreras and UGT led protests in 55 cities across
Spain today, El Mundo newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Esteban Duarte in Madrid at 
